The Qinghai-Tibet Plateau has an indispensable element: the people living in Sanjiangyuan area. They are full of love for Mother Nature. Jang Tendar is one of them. Watch the video to learn more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Sanjiangyuan series In the Sanjiangyuan Series, we present the stunning landscapes and abundant wildlife of the Sanjiangyuan Region, where the Yangtze, Yellow and Lancang rivers all originate. Sanjiangyuan has earned the title "Water tower of China," because the abundant glacier resources here have a freshwater reserve of 200 billion cubic meters. The precious water has nurtured numerous wild flora and fauna like snow leopards, Himalayan blue sheep, Thorold's deer, Tibetan wild asses, and vultures. List of episodes Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep.1: Sources of Life Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 2: Jinsha River Overture Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 3: Alpine Wetlands Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 4: Dancers on the Cliff Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 5: Thorold's Deer Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 6: Elves in the Snow Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 7: Plateau Wanderers Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 8: King of the Sky Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 9: Prince of Snow Mountains (Cover image a video screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)